reviews.text: It’s a popular restaurant with unusual food ordering process. Walked in at around 630 Sunday night, it’s already rather booked out without many tables left. From the moment you picking the piece of steak to the moment they served it to you, the process is completely visible. With much confidence in the quality of the meat, I guess chef became less attentive in cooking. I had a piece of tenderloin for medium rare but it tasted rather dry. Also too much salt was added. It would be nice to leave it plainer so customers can adjust the flavour by ourselves. Then, I had the creamy garlic mushrooms as the side dish. The texture of the sauce  wasn’t thick. Yet, mushrooms are rather fresh as they were juicy with a nice firm texture. All in all, the food is still agreeable and the dinning experience was special.

Really unique experience you can go in and choose your meat and they will cook it for you. We went there three time during our stay in HK.

We had the steak, burger and brunch. The Mac and cheese was really tasty but the burger... It's one of the best burgers I have ever eaten freaking delicious it's a MUST try.

It’s quite a unique experience to pick your meat right from the butcher and have the restaurant immediately cook it for you. We had tenderloin and sirloin steak. The veggies were also very fresh. it was an enjoyable experience overall.

It was great place! My husband and I really liked this place, but each time it gets worse and worse, the menu changes and with it the quality of products and service!  the avocado toast was moldy and the waitress pretended not to see her, we asked Benedict with salmon eggs, brought us bacon and asked to order differently because she did not hear🤔they brought coffee after the meal....sooo...the mood was spoiled! we did't pay for avocado toast and coffee was given to us in order, but ...so sad😕
Excellent steaks and lovely house wines. You don't need much more but to be honest, the sides are all wonderful too and the service is attentive.

reviews.text:
서비스나 분위기 다 너무 좋았습니다
이런거 앵간해서 안적는데 
가격대비 느모느모 잘 묵고 와서 씁니다
여자 혼자 맥주까지 300홍콩 달러 정도면 배터지게 먹고와요
스테이크가 너무 먹고싶었는데 
Blt를 저번에 가봤어서 어디를갈까 고민했는데
탁월한 결정이었습니다
창가쪽은 예약자들이있어 못앉았고
혼자가면 또 앉을수없었던것 같아요. 
10프로의 서비스 차지가 함께 부가되며
고기 선택후 60불? 정도를 추가 지불하면 소스와 사이드 디쉬를 선택가능합니다
저는 후기를 읽고 메쉬드 포테이토 선택했습니다 소스는 추천 받았어요
고기랑 함께 얹어 먹으면 꿀맛!

It’s a popular restaurant with unusual food ordering process. Walked in at around 630 Sunday night, it’s already rather booked out without many tables left. From the moment you picking the piece of steak to the moment they served it to you, the process is completely visible. With much confidence in the quality of the meat, I guess chef became less attentive in cooking. I had a piece of tenderloin for medium rare but it tasted rather dry. Also too much salt was added. It would be nice to leave it plainer so customers can adjust the flavour by ourselves. Then, I had the creamy garlic mushrooms as the side dish. The texture of the sauce  wasn’t thick. Yet, mushrooms are rather fresh as they were juicy with a nice firm texture. All in all, the food is still agreeable and the dinning experience was special.

如发现了新天地一般晚餐和早餐都选择了这一家

晚餐的牛排🥩肉肉特色么有尝试到所以更加期待下一次再去

早餐的BAken beans也超级棒

热辣辣的番茄焗豆拌着培根瞬间有辛辣的刺激和软硬结合的口感

咖啡一般可是太少我想要一大大杯才够唤醒我的早晨

店员小姐姐们都非常亲切

还有个小超市，内容都是比较偏不常见的哦。

可以打开多次，尝试各种。期待期待！

坐落在大馬路旁，外觀充滿歐陸風格。
店員是說英文的，餐牌也是全英文的，但由於菜式下附以詳細解說，所以理解不成問題。
Main Course點了五成熟的Lamb Burger及Full English。
甜品則選了Bread and Butter Pudding.
1) Full English 很快便送上，與在英倫吃過的All Day Breakfast 風味很接近，非常好吃，Chipolata 色澤鮮明，外層結層，香味濃郁；hash brown炸得脆身，但調味不足; 其他配菜水準不俗，值得一試
2) Lamb Burger: 朋友本想試3成熟，但店員很細心地推介5成熟較具風味，我們從善如流，香滑牛油的融入香脆的漢堡包內，令人一試難
忘，羊肉雖然算新鮮，但味道則不過不失，薯條配合意大利茄醬，令人食指大動。
3）Bread Pudding: 第一口已覺得，真的太甜了，唯一補不足的地方是，布甸上的青檸雪著芭。
以西餐來說，價錢合理，是令人滿意的一頓午餐，西環的食肆真是驚喜處處。

Really unique experience you can go in and choose your meat and they will cook it for you. We went there three time during our stay in HK.

We had the steak, burger and brunch. The Mac and cheese was really tasty but the burger... It's one of the best burgers I have ever eaten freaking delicious it's a MUST try.

reviews.text:
滷水鵝肝很嫩滑，比附近的潮州名店德記做得好。鵝肉撈粗麵稍淡，麵條也淋了一點，沒有咬勁。煎𧐢烙是半煎炸囗感軟淋那種，自己較喜歡吃炸得香脆的港式蠔餅。店員推介餐廳菠蘿咕嚕肉(!)，酸甜味道調校得不俗，咕嚕肉肥瘦適中。

當晚只有數枱客人，環境清靜，很適合和朋友飯聚談天說地。餐廳樓底很高，裝修雅緻，地方整潔新淨，坐得很舒服，店員也很友善健談，整晚不斷為我們添茶。

光顧日期：2019年7月11日
两個人點了一客鵝肉鵝肝雙拼、香煎蠔烙和鵝肉撈麵。上菜時見碟頭 不大，決定追加，待應姐姐推介了咕嚕肉，潮菜館做咕噜竟然都得。除香煎蠔烙外，其他食物都好吃，不過两個人四碟，原來都幾多的。

Food was average while the service was lacking.
But you do get welcoming tea on arrival but they charge you $8 per head automatically.
Was also annoyed they kept trying to sell us cocktails because it was BOGOF.
Nice food and nice service.

The restaurant was great. Excellent service and great food with fine prices. However when I ordered the fried oyster egg there was a hard object which I chewed on and hurt a lot. I would assume it's an oyster shell they did compensate and gave another plate. But at the end, my favourite chiuchow cuisine is still chiu chow garden in causeway bay. 潮江春。
